constraints_details.result: Hinterland Lower Lea Valley including Stratford

description: Demolition of all existing buildings and erection of buildings ranging from three to six storeys, comprising 10,306 sq. m. (GIA) of class C3 residential floorspace (101 dwellings) and 1,405 sq. m. (GIA) of class B1 business floorspace and the creation of a new vehicular access from Elderflower Way alterations to existing vehicular and pedestrian access from Romford Road together with the provision of associated car parking, cycle spaces, refuse and recycling storage and the creation of new areas of open space and landscaping. *THIS APPLICATION IS LOCATED WITHIN STRATFORD ST JOHNS CONSERVATION AREA *THIS APPLICATION AFFECTS THE SETTING OF LISTED BUILDINGS/STRUCTURES (The Old Dispensary at 30 Romford Road, St Johns Church, St Johns Church railings, St John's Road at 2 Romford Road, 49 Broadway, Martyrs memorial, King Edward Pub at 47 Broadway, Gurney Memorial, Stratford Town Hall, Stratford Court House, 3 x K6 telephone kiosks outside Stratford Town Hall)
